# Bad-record handling — the `mode` option

## When a row doesn't match the schema

- **`PERMISSIVE`** *(default)* — null out the failed columns, **keep the row**
  - With `columnNameOfCorruptRecord`, the raw bad string is stored there
- **`DROPMALFORMED`** — silently drop the bad row
- **`FAILFAST`** — throw on the first bad row

## For production

- **`badRecordsPath`** — write rejected rows to their own location for offline inspection
- Keeps the pipeline running while still capturing what it skipped
